00:52:46.050 --> 00:52:47.650
gets easy to be repeated.

00:52:47.650 --> 00:52:51.160
But even having seen
some success 20 days,

00:52:51.160 --> 00:52:52.630
30 days, I always
sort of fall off.

00:52:52.630 --> 00:52:55.300
Do you have any specific
tips for turning it

00:52:55.300 --> 00:52:57.020
into a long-term habit?

00:52:57.020 --> 00:52:57.790
DAN HARRIS: Yeah.

00:52:57.790 --> 00:53:00.150
I wrote a whole
chapter about this

00:53:00.150 --> 00:53:01.920
because this is one of the big--

00:53:01.920 --> 00:53:04.110
there are many people
in your situation.

00:53:09.160 --> 00:53:11.160
So there are a lot of
people who've never tried.

00:53:11.160 --> 00:53:12.930
They just can't get it started.

00:53:12.930 --> 00:53:15.000
And then there are some
people who try and just

00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:16.380
fall off really quickly.

00:53:16.380 --> 00:53:18.914
And then there are people
like you who, they try.

00:53:18.914 --> 00:53:19.830
They see the benefits.

00:53:19.830 --> 00:53:21.480
And they still fall off.

00:53:21.480 --> 00:53:22.470
The thing to know--

00:53:22.470 --> 00:53:23.350
well, there are a bunch
of things to know.

00:53:23.350 --> 00:53:24.650
One is that we are not--

00:53:24.650 --> 00:53:26.640
I talked before about
evolution and how

00:53:26.640 --> 00:53:28.265
it bequeathed us a racing mind.

00:53:28.265 --> 00:53:29.640
It also bequeathed
us a mind that

00:53:29.640 --> 00:53:33.840
is shit at creating
healthy habits.

00:53:33.840 --> 00:53:35.710
We evolved, as I
discussed before,

00:53:35.710 --> 00:53:41.160
to spot saber-toothed tigers
and find where the food was.

00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:44.310
Evolution didn't care about
your long-term health.

00:53:44.310 --> 00:53:48.720
It just cared about getting your
DNA into the next generation.

00:53:48.720 --> 00:53:52.680
So we're not wired for brushing
our teeth and things like that.

00:53:52.680 --> 00:53:54.780
We are wired, as a
consequence of evolution,

00:53:54.780 --> 00:53:57.450
for really kind of
short-term thinking.

00:53:57.450 --> 00:54:03.690
And so just knowing that lowers
the temperature a little bit.

00:54:03.690 --> 00:54:05.290
You know you're wired to fail.

00:54:05.290 --> 00:54:06.420
This is hard to do.

00:54:06.420 --> 00:54:08.620
You are going to fail
time and time again.

00:54:08.620 --> 00:54:13.560
And so the answer is to
approach the entire enterprise

00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:19.130
with a spirit of exploration
and experimentation.

00:54:19.130 --> 00:54:21.770
And so try different
times of day.

00:54:21.770 --> 00:54:22.940
Try different apps.

00:54:22.940 --> 00:54:24.980
Try different kinds
of meditation.

00:54:24.980 --> 00:54:26.540
Try different dosages.

00:54:26.540 --> 00:54:29.570
Like maybe really it'd be
better for you to do one minute.

00:54:29.570 --> 00:54:31.350
Maybe five minutes is good.

00:54:31.350 --> 00:54:34.790
Try drafting off
of existing habits.

00:54:34.790 --> 00:54:39.270
Maybe you have an
abiding exercise habit.

00:54:39.270 --> 00:54:41.840
Well, right after
you stretch, if you

00:54:41.840 --> 00:54:45.350
could put meditation
right on there,

00:54:45.350 --> 00:54:49.810
it might be a good
way to get it going.

00:54:49.810 --> 00:54:52.560
So two parts here, one,
don't beat yourself up.

00:54:52.560 --> 00:54:53.780
It's totally normal.

00:54:53.780 --> 00:54:56.240
Two, try a bunch of
stuff, like those things

00:54:56.240 --> 00:54:58.345
that I just listed,
and see what happens.

00:54:58.345 --> 00:55:02.270
And I think over time, given
that you see the benefits,

00:55:02.270 --> 00:55:05.990
and you have a history
of making it work,

00:55:05.990 --> 00:55:07.280
it will click at some point.

00:55:07.280 --> 00:55:07.820
It will.

00:55:07.820 --> 00:55:09.076
AUDIENCE: Thanks.

00:55:09.076 --> 00:55:10.700
DAN HARRIS: And the
other thing to know

00:55:10.700 --> 00:55:14.570
is that starting,
falling off the wagon,

00:55:14.570 --> 00:55:18.110
and starting again, in that
process, nothing has been lost.

00:55:18.110 --> 00:55:22.250
It's not like you are
rebuilding from zero.

00:55:22.250 --> 00:55:23.820
I don't think that's the case.

00:55:23.820 --> 00:55:27.974
It's just like when you
get lost in meditation.

00:55:27.974 --> 00:55:30.140
The whole game is just to
notice and to start again.

00:55:30.140 --> 00:55:32.870
And I think that that analogy
holds true for the habit

00:55:32.870 --> 00:55:33.640
formation process.

