00:59:18.640 --> 00:59:23.560
I'm not going to do it,
at least not right now.

00:59:23.560 --> 00:59:27.260
But as to just the
everyday quote unquote,

00:59:27.260 --> 00:59:30.610
"vices," drinking alcohol,
smoking a little bit of weed,

00:59:30.610 --> 00:59:32.770
or whatever it is,
I am not really

00:59:32.770 --> 00:59:35.440
that judgmental about it.

00:59:35.440 --> 00:59:40.510
The Buddhist perspective is
not that you should never

00:59:40.510 --> 00:59:42.320
have any pleasure in your life.

00:59:42.320 --> 00:59:47.260
It's are you so
swamped and addicted

00:59:47.260 --> 00:59:49.270
to the pleasure that
it's actually really

00:59:49.270 --> 00:59:51.610
not pleasurable anymore?

00:59:51.610 --> 00:59:53.980
And that's the
line to play with.

00:59:53.980 --> 01:00:02.399
So I know plenty of really,
really well-trained meditation

01:00:02.399 --> 01:00:04.690
teachers who will have a
glass of wine once in a while,

01:00:04.690 --> 01:00:07.060
or like chocolate, or whatever.

01:00:07.060 --> 01:00:10.375
The point is not that you
should become an ascetic.

01:00:10.375 --> 01:00:11.980
The point is that
you should just

01:00:11.980 --> 01:00:15.664
be able to manage these
pleasures skillfully.

01:00:15.664 --> 01:00:17.080
And actually, you
can start to see

01:00:17.080 --> 01:00:23.000
over time that desire,
pleasure, these

01:00:23.000 --> 01:00:25.010
are all impermanent things.

01:00:25.010 --> 01:00:28.617
And you can start to surf
that and get interested in it

01:00:28.617 --> 01:00:30.950
in a way that the meditation
practice can help you with.

01:00:30.950 --> 01:00:34.460
And on the flip side,
displeasure and pain

01:00:34.460 --> 01:00:37.800
are also impermanent.

01:00:37.800 --> 01:00:40.820
So the practice can be
woven into all sorts

01:00:40.820 --> 01:00:42.440
of aspects of life.

01:00:42.440 --> 01:00:44.499
And I would argue that we're--

01:00:44.499 --> 01:00:46.790
I have a friend who's a
neuroscientist and a meditation

01:00:46.790 --> 01:00:47.070
teacher.

01:00:47.070 --> 01:00:48.650
And he was writing a
book that he ended up

01:00:48.650 --> 01:00:49.608
calling something else.

01:00:49.608 --> 01:00:52.130
But he was going to call
it "We're All Addicted."

01:00:52.130 --> 01:00:53.300
Because we're all addicted.

01:00:53.300 --> 01:00:55.040
Addiction is part of our lives.

01:00:55.040 --> 01:00:57.410
We're just hurling
ourselves from one hit

01:00:57.410 --> 01:01:00.530
of pleasant experience, one
dopamine hit, to the next

01:01:00.530 --> 01:01:02.180
all the time--

01:01:02.180 --> 01:01:05.240
one latte, one slice of
cake, one party, whatever.

01:01:05.240 --> 01:01:06.890
We're always on the hunt.

01:01:06.890 --> 01:01:10.070
And seeing that
is the first step

01:01:10.070 --> 01:01:13.460
towards starting to kind of play
with it in a more skillful way.

01:01:13.460 --> 01:01:15.860
It doesn't mean that
you are never going

01:01:15.860 --> 01:01:17.870
to have any pleasurable stuff.

